.TH "kernel_sendmsg_locked" 9 "kernel_sendmsg_locked" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernel_sendmsg_locked \- send a message through @sock (kernel-space)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kernel_sendmsg_locked
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ","
.BI "struct kvec *vec "  ","
.BI "size_t num "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
sock
.IP "msg" 12
message header
.IP "vec" 12
output s/g array
.IP "num" 12
output s/g array length
.IP "size" 12
total message data size

Builds the message data with \fIvec\fP and sends it through \fIsock\fP.
Returns the number of bytes sent, or an error code.
Caller must hold \fIsk\fP.
